Interface AssociationConstraintService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    StandardAssociationConstraintService

    @RemoteInterface
public interface AssociationConstraintService
    Manages AssociationConstraint and AssociationConstraintItem objects and validations.

    Supported API: true

    Extendable: false

      • getInconsistentLinkTypeForSameRoleATypeAndSameBaseLinkType

        java.lang.String getInconsistentLinkTypeForSameRoleATypeAndSameBaseLinkType(AssociationConstraintItem targetItem,
                                                                            java.util.Collection otherItems)
                                                                     throws WTException
        Ensure that the targetItem and the otherItems are consistent: if they have the same RoleAType and the same base LinkType, then they should also have the same linkType. This ensures that the UI can determine which type of link to create given only the knowledge of the RoleAType and the base linkType. This capability was originally created for WTPartUsageLink, but could be used for other links, too.

        Supported API: true
        Parameters:
        targetItem - The item being compared to the otherItems.
        otherItems - The other items being compared to the targetItem.
        Returns:
        String
        Throws:
        WTException

      • getInconsistentLinkTypeForSameRoleATypeAndSameBaseLinkType

        java.lang.String getInconsistentLinkTypeForSameRoleATypeAndSameBaseLinkType(AssociationConstraintItem targetItem)
                                                                     throws WTException
        Ensure that the targetItem and the items already in the database are consistent: if they have the same RoleAType and the same base LinkType, then they should also have the same linkType. This ensures that the UI can determine which type of link to create given only the knowledge of the RoleAType and the base linkType. This capability was originally created for WTPartUsageLink, but could be used for other links, too.

        Supported API: true
        Parameters:
        targetItem - The item being compared to the items in the database.
        Returns:
        String
        Throws:
        WTException
